<br>
The 10k (9k if you don't go white or black) Horse is Slower then Jboots or run3.<br>
<br>
I raced someone with jboots with em after they said their 2boxed cleric can't quite keep up on a horse. It's NOT just acceleration.<br>
<br>
It's not much slower. You need to run a little bit before you aren't convinced it's your imagination.<br>
<br>
Just to add confirmation to click/med while on a horse, I was trying my best to burn out my White Ceramic Band on the latest CT Mage Raid while waiting for enough mana to cast a nuke after a rez. It works.<br>
<br>
9k horse is so worth it. I see people die all the time sitting, while I'm on my high horse medding away. 30k, IMO, you'd be better off saving 25k and getting Jboots MQ or Tboots.<br>
100k, I don't have, but would if I had the cash, in an instant, just for the travel. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uarmantuneweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arman Tuneweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#333333>(10/6/02 2:12:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1039.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Simple Horse Question</span><hr size=1> I whole-heartedly agree with Lobaner, last night I saw my horse conversing with a gnome about a plot to take over the world.  Evil gnomes, evil horsies . . ..  And yeah, their beady eyes do look kinda scary . . . . .<br>
