As for the graphic - making yourself invis and turning off invis makes the head disappear, but you seem to 'drop' to the floor again too (yet changing cameraview, the horse is still there, but the head's back too once back in first person view)...  <br>
Is there another way to permanently remove the horse's head from view - because going invis and back poofs yer pet, and I like to see around myself with different cameraview depending where I am to see if an monsters or beasts are nearby to attack me (instead of turning 360 around to keep a constant lookout).<br>
<br>
And what are the known zones horses don't work in?  Any and all dungeons?  Nexus?  any others?<br>
<br>
Oh yeah, and what about food/drink for the horse?  how does that work?  I got some Misty Thicket Picknicks and Qeynos Afternoon Tea's packed for the extra stats (eating manually) - but does the horse snack from my summoned bread/water or does it eat the picknicks/drink the teas?<br>
<br>
Thanks for any answers forthcoming... <p>Yanari Pethugger,<br>
Gnome - not a snack<br>
