<br>
However, summonings of the faster horses can vary in how <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;pokey&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> they are, i.e., how long they take to start at stop.  About a third to a half or more are decidely <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;pokey,&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> they take a lot of room to start and stop.  This is awful when you are pulling, and makes various forms of kiting quite dangerous.  Maybe a third to a fifth are acceptable, and can be used to kite.  From a sixth to a tenth are sweet: they start and stop on a dime.  It may also be the case that the less pokey the horse is, the faster its maximum speed, but I have not been able to verify it.<br>
<br>
In my opinion, only the 10K or the 100K ponees are worth it.  The 10K ponee gets you the meditation benefits, but the middle horses I think I would rather buy <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Spirit of the Wolf</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> potions for the price difference.  But the 100K ponee is a dream, especially the best summon.  It is like flying almost.  I can pull, kite, lose adds, and so on.<br>
<br>
It is also almost like having a couple extra spell slots.  Since I don't have to sit to get to my spell book, I can hot-swap spells in combat safely.<br>
<br>
The horse's head is in the way, but I have gotten used to it.  First of all, I turn one-quarter away from my target or the fight, which makes targetting much easier.  I use assist a lot, for example to re-target whatever <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Gobaner</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is attacking, I have a hot-key:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>/pet target<br>
/say The verdict is GUILTY!  The sentence is DEATH!<br>
/assist</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
(I have voice graft)<br>
<br>
For looting corpses, I target the corpse at a distance, approach the corpse on my horse, and use a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>/loot</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> hot key.<br>
<br>
All in all, I feel I have adapted to the horses head well enough, although I understand that some will be frustrated.  But the powers it grants are well worth it, especially avoiding sitting and increased mana regeneration.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Razamatazz Pizzazz</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
